- The term "top-spending customer" refers to the customer with the highest total sales amount;
- The time period "during the year 2016" refers to the date range from January 1, 2016, to December 31, 2016;
- "New York, USA" specifies the city and country where the customer is located.

- "top spenders" refers to regions with the highest total spending;
- `total_spent` is the sum of all customer spending within a region;
- `avg_loyalty_points` is the average loyalty points accumulated by customers in a region.

- "Most fruitful" refers to the category with the highest average profit per product;
- "Blossoms above the garden's mean" means the average profit is greater than the average profit across all categories;
- "Total sales exceed a thousand" means the total sales for the category are more than 1000;
- "Number of unique products is more than five" means the category contains more than 5 products.

- "lighthouses, shining the brightest" refers to regions with the highest average order value;
- "customer segments" are groups of customers categorized by their purchasing behavior or demographic characteristics;
- "average order value" is the mean amount spent per order in a specific region and segment.

- 'Delivered consumer orders' refers to orders that have been successfully shipped and received by customers in the 'consumer' segment;
- 'First 100 days of the year' refers to the initial 100 days in the sales data, likely corresponding to the start of the fiscal or calendar year;
- 'Harvest of over $1000 in sales' means the total sales in each category and region must exceed $1000.

- "Customer segments" refer to groups of customers categorized based on their purchasing behavior or other characteristics;
- "Blossomed with total sales exceeding a thousand dollars" means the total sales for the segment are greater than $1000;
- "Average price per unit" is the mean price of each unit of the product sold.

- 'shone the brightest' refers to the highest total spending;
- 'peers' refers to other customers in the same segment;
- 'Consumer' segment refers to individual or household customers.

- 'Consumer' segment refers to individual customers rather than corporate or business customers;
- 'Website' as the order source indicates that the orders were placed through an online platform;
- 'Total spent' is the sum of the total price of all items in the orders;
- 'Average profit' is calculated by averaging the profit made from each order item;
- 'Quantity > 1' means each order must contain more than one unit of a product.

- "Wealthiest customers" refers to the region with the highest average total spent by customers;
- "Ratio of total sales to the average spending" is calculated as the total sales in the region divided by the average total spent by customers in that region;
- "Top 10 products" means the products with the highest values in the calculated ratio.

- "Fertile regions" refers to regions with high total sales;
- "Yielding the highest total sales" means the regions with the greatest total sales amount;
- "Bountiful regions" refers to regions with high sales and order counts;
- "Average value of each order" is calculated by dividing the total sales by the total number of orders.

- 'Most loyal customers' refers to those with the highest loyalty points in the loyalty program;
- 'Average value of their orders' is calculated as the average total amount of orders for each customer segment;
- 'Most valuable segment' refers to the customer segment with the highest total sales.

- "Top customers" refers to customers with the highest total spending;
- "Most popular products" refers to products with the highest total sales;
- "Average order value by segment" is the average amount spent per order for customers within the same segment.
